FBIS4-10800 "drlat075_a_94021" FBIS-LAT-94-075 Daily Report 18 Apr 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Raul Castro Sends Letter of Recognition to Canecutters Raul Castro Sends Letter of Recognition to Canecutters FL1804235194 Havana Cuba Vision Network in Spanish 2220 GMT 18 Apr 94 FL1804235194 Havana Cuba Vision Network Spanish BFN [Text] Army General Raul Castro Ruz, minister of the Revolutionary Armed Forces, has sent a letter of recognition to members of the the Roberto Rodriguez brigade of volunteer canecutters for their achievements in the current harvest. This brigade is cutting cane in Camaguey Province, which was awarded millionaire status in the manual cutting of sugarcane. In the province of Camaguey, 25 brigades of canecutters have managed to cut one million arrobas during the current harvest, while another group is on their way to cutting a third million. Considering these results, Camaguey has obtained the status of millionaire in manual canecutting. [Begin unidentified worker recording] All comrades here are willing to cut to the last sugarcane for this harvest. This shows that victory is achieved when there is the willingness and desire to fight for this Revolution and to bail the country out of its current situation. [end recording]
